	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=164398><span id= >Khift</span></a><br><span id=notbold>39 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.73]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>If you want to become accepted in Paineel and you don't care about your Erudin faction and are above level 35 (Which you should be, seeing as you're working on your epic), then just cast Gather Shadows and enter Erudin. From there take the teleporter to the main city, and pull the patrolling guards that walk past the entrance to the cave w/ the teleporters. The guards are all level 30 Paladins, excluding the ones outside. They give massive negative hits with Erudin factions and a very good positive hit with the Heretics. I've heard that within a few hours of doing this you can get all the way to and past Indifferent with the Heretics.<br><br>But anyways, I've been inside Paineel, and to reach Duriek Bloodpool you don't even pass any guards beyond the lvl 6 Skeleton guards on the outside. And if you're scared of those, then you shouldn't be working on your epic yet. You should be back in the Field of Bone killing scorpions.<br><br>As for Neriak faction, well, that could be a problem. As stated above, what seems to be the best way to do this is by turning in four full stacks of wine to The Scribe of Innoruuk in Neriak Third Gate. Getting to the Scribe may be a problem though, seeing as I'd be extremely surprised if there was a way to beehive your way through Neriak Third Gate without finding a single NPC that can't see through invis (Most inhabitants of Neriak Third Gate are casters).&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>You also might have to have good faction with Neriak Ogres too, seeing as Smaka is an ogre and is in Neriak. There is no real way I can see to raise that faction that is listed. Yes, it does list one quest that raises it, but that involves Chef Dooga, whom no matter what your faction is with Ogguk, is KoS to everyone but Ogres, Trolls and Dark Elves. Or so I've heard, I can't say I've found that out myself.<br><br>I have no idea if Smaka is on Neriak Ogre faction though. I checked that faction on this site and only found two NPC's in Neriak that are listed as being on the faction, and that is Spice and Jacker. I think if it was epic-oriented then someone would've posted about it already though, so maybe I'm just being pessimistic about this whole thing. Probably.<br><br>Anyways, GL getting your epic. I'm sure as heck looking forward to it =).<br><br>Edit: It's Erudin, not Eruding! Doh!<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Sep 17 19:08:09 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>A sunflower scowls at you, ready to attack -- what would you like your tombstone to say?<br>A sunflower kicks YOU for 22 damage!<br><br>Varukisas Jadescale, 40th Iksar Monk<br>Tarew Marr<br>&lt;House of Elder&gt</td></tr>
